'''Tânia Tomé''' (born Tania Teresa Tomé on November 11, 1981, in Maputo, Mozambique) is a  public speaker,[[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], author, [[Coaching|life coach]],[[economist]],tv personality, singer, poet and lyricist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.expressodasilhas.sapo.cv/economia/item/52589-tania-tome-se-um-empreendedor-nao-for-bom-lider-e-apenas-um-empresario|title=Tânia Tomé: Se um empreendedor não for bom líder é apenas um empresário - Expresso das Ilhas|last=Ilhas|first=Jorge Montezinho, Expresso das|website=www.expressodasilhas.sapo.cv|language=pl|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://portal.dnb.de/opac.htm?method=simpleSearch&cqlMode=true&query=idn=1037055322|title=Katalog der Deutschen Nationalbibliothek|website=portal.dnb.de|language=de|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref>

== Biography ==
Tânia Tomé is public figure in Mozambique who advocates for positive social change, entrepreneurship and leadership ecosystem. She has won several international awards, including the award of excellence awarded to her by [[Mozambique|Mozambican]] President. She also was the recipient for the Portugal Academic Award by former [[Portugal|Portuguese]] President [[Mário Soares]].She established the Ecokaya company and currently heads the organization's board of directors.Tânia has met and interacted with more six living Presidents worldwide and many leaders worldwide. She had the opportunity to be an executive and leadership coach giving sessions to multinational and big companies. Also, Tânia had an opportunity to be the first young godmother of the biggest private University in Mozambique. In addition, she did start in her own inspirational coaching session with a concept that she developed called Succenergy to empower people, entrepreneurs and leaders that led to her [[TED (conference)|TED]] talk.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lionessesofafrica.com/blog/2017/12/10/startup-story-of-tania-tome|title=Tânia Tomé: a Mozambican serial entrepreneur using her skills to train and develop a new generation of business leaders in Africa -Lioness of Africa|last=Africa|first=Melanie Hawken, Lioness of |website=www.lionessesofafrica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-10}}</ref> She also volunteered to work for the NGO Education for Development as President, a community program with the personal support of President [[Barack Obama]] Pepfar Funds. She is the vice-president of the Non-Governmental-Organisation Green, a project created to promote the role of entrepreneurship, SDG projects and young, women in business. She is a bank and  investment professional with more than 12 years experience and holds a Economic Degree and Pos-graduation in Management and Auditory  [[Catholic University of Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yali.nd.edu/blog/page/2/|title=Blog // The Mandela Washington Fellowship // University of Notre Dame|last=Dame|first=ENR // Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre|website=The Mandela Washington Fellowship|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=José|first=Matope|title=Tânia Tomé eleita uma das personalidades mais influentes de África - MMO|url=https://noticias.mmo.co.mz/2017/08/tania-tome-eleita-uma-das-personalidades-mais-influentes-de-africa.html|language=pt-PT|accessdate=2017-11-19}}</ref>

Among 1000 young leaders from around the world, Tânia Tomé was named the 2016 Young African Leader, a title conferred on her by President Obama Iniative the Washington and Mandela Fellowship. Also in August 2015, she was awarded the title of Outstanding Business Leader by the US Government during the International Entrepreneurship Summit, which was attended by [[Kenya]]n President [[Jomo Kenyatta|Kenyatta]] and US President Barack Obama.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tve24.com/sociedade/barack-obama-nomea-mocambicana-tania-tome-young-african-leader-2016/|title=Barack OBama nomea moçambicana Tânia Tomé como Young African Leader 2016|last=Redacçao|date=2016-06-05|work=TVE24|access-date=2017-11-19|language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://yali.nd.edu/#flw_46070|title=Home // The Mandela Washington Fellowship // University of Notre Dame|last=Dame|first=ENR // Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre|website=The Mandela Washington Fellowship|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref>

